## Examples — delete the ones you don't need

> Pick the block that matches your business, paste it above, and tune it.

### Simple 3-stage funnel

```markdown
Stages: lead → opportunity → closed (won|lost)
Qualified: decision-maker confirmed AND budget in range.
Sources: referral | inbound | outbound
```

### Long enterprise cycle

```markdown
Stages: new → contacted → discovery → qualified → proposal → negotiation → won|lost
Qualified: full MEDDIC (Metrics, Economic buyer, Decision criteria,
           Decision process, Identify pain, Champion).
Sources: referral | inbound | event | outbound | partner | expansion
```

---

## Note on co-mounted modules

When a lead reaches **won**, the hand-offs below fire only if the sibling
module is mounted — all soft, never a hard dependency:

- `rasa.module.contracts` — the won deal becomes a signed contract (same
  `@acct-<slug>` handle).
- `rasa.module.field-log` — a kickoff visit / first field entry against the
  same account.

If neither is mounted, the lead still closes cleanly — it just sits at
`won` in your ledger.
